    "Roland Michel was a student of <a href=\"/chastela\">Andr\u00e9 Chastel</a> who received her master\u2019s degree at the Sorbonne in 1959 with a thesis on the still life and genre painter Anne Vallayer-Coster (1744-1818).": [],
    "This artist served as the subject of Roland Michel\u2019s first article that appeared in <em>Burlington Magazine</em> in 1960, and of the later monograph, Anne Vallayer-Coster (1970).": [
