    "She also wrote exhibition reviews that appeared in journals like <em>Master Drawings</em> as well as the <em>Burlington Magazine</em>.": [],
    "Alongside her work as a dealer, Roland Michel published widely as a scholar of eighteenth-century art in French and Anglo-American journals and museum catalogs.": [],
    "In 2002-2003, Roland Michel organized the first and only solo retrospective exhibition on Vallayer-Coster, <em>Anne Vallayer-Coster: Painter to the Court of Marie Antoinette</em>, that travelled from the National Gallery of Art in Washington, D.C.": [
